  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate", 
    "date": "2020-03-18T04:00:00Z", 
    "text": "Coronavirus Credit Expansion Act\n\nThis bill increases the maximum loan amount for a small business disaster loan made in response to COVID-19 (i.e., coronavirus disease 2019), and it requires the Small Business Administration to expedite the loan approval process for such loans.\n\nThe fine for a conviction relating to a fraudulent claim for the payment or approval of such a loan shall be three times the amount of the loan."
